I'm particularly grateful that my bill, the Retain Skilled Vets Act, was included in the passed legislation. This bill repeals the 180-day rule for retiring servicemembers, increasing civilian employment opportunities for veterans & retaining institutional expertise in the DOD.

It authorizes $240M to reduce out-of-pocket housing expenses & rent, nearly $200M for construction of new barracks, & $120M for off-installation childcare centers. It helps spouse employment by expanding reimbursements for relicensing, business costs, & certification reciprocity.

This bill is a great win for @HAFB. The NDAA fully funds the Sentinel program to modernize the land-based leg of the nuclear triad and bring nearly 4,000 jobs to Northern Utah as the first major Department of Defense acquisition program based out of HAFB.

Today I voted for the NDAA, a robust & comprehensive bill that will promote innovation, strengthen our readiness & capabilities, provide for military families, counter the CCP, & ensure that the DoD can focus on honing its core competencies & competitive advantages.  üßµ‚¨áÔ∏è
